---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BlogPosting",
  "headline": "Top 10 TikTok Video Editing Tips for Better Content",
  "description": "Expert tips for editing TikTok videos to increase engagement and views.",
  "datePublished": "2024-01-10",
  "dateModified": "2024-01-10",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "SaveDownloadTT"
  }
};
---

<Layout
  title="Top 10 TikTok Video Editing Tips | Expert Guide"
  description="Master TikTok video editing with our top 10 expert tips. Learn how to create engaging content that gets more views and likes."
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />

  <main class="pt-32 px-4">
    <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">
        Top 10 TikTok Video <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-500 to-pink-500 text-transparent bg-clip-text">Editing Tips</span>
      </h1>
      
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-gray-400 mb-12">
        <time datetime="2024-01-10">January 10, 2024</time>
        <span>â€¢</span>
        <span>8 min read</span>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none">
        <h2>1. Perfect Your Timing</h2>
        <p>Timing is crucial in TikTok videos. Learn to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Sync transitions with music beats</li>
          <li>Use precise cuts for better flow</li>
          <li>Time effects with audio cues</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. Master Transitions</h2>
        <p>Smooth transitions keep viewers engaged:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Hand transitions</li>
          <li>Whip transitions</li>
          <li>Jump cuts</li>
          <li>Spin transitions</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Use Text Effectively</h2>
        <p>Text can enhance your message:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Keep text concise</li>
          <li>Use readable fonts</li>
          <li>Time text appearance with content</li>
          <li>Add captions for accessibility</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Optimize Sound</h2>
        <p>Audio quality matters:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Use trending sounds</li>
          <li>Balance voice-over and background music</li>
          <li>Add sound effects strategically</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Color Grading</h2>
        <p>Make your videos visually appealing:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Use consistent filters</li>
          <li>Adjust brightness and contrast</li>
          <li>Create a signature look</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Perfect Your Cuts</h2>
        <p>Clean cuts make professional videos:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Remove dead space</li>
          <li>Use jump cuts effectively</li>
          <li>Match action across cuts</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Add Effects Strategically</h2>
        <p>Don't overdo effects:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Use effects to enhance content</li>
          <li>Keep effects consistent</li>
          <li>Test new effects before posting</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Optimize Video Length</h2>
        <p>Keep viewers engaged:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Start strong in first 3 seconds</li>
          <li>Keep videos concise</li>
          <li>End with a hook</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>9. Use Trending Features</h2>
        <p>Stay current with TikTok trends:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Duets and Stitches</li>
          <li>Green Screen effects</li>
          <li>New TikTok features</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>10. Quality Check</h2>
        <p>Before posting, verify:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Video quality</li>
          <li>Sound synchronization</li>
          <li>Text readability</li>
          <li>Overall flow</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>